Summary of `ebstopcode' Options
*******************************

   The `ebstopcode' command supports both traditional single-letter
options and mnemonic long option names.  Long option names are
indicated with `--' instead of `-'.  Abbreviations for option names are
allowed as long as they are unique.

`-c CODE'
`--code CODE'
     Specify CODE as text stop code (e.g. "0x1f09 0x0001").
     `ebstopcode' displays text until CODE is appeared.

`-h'
`--help'
     Output help message to standard out, then exit.

`-l LENGTH'
`--text-length LENGTH'
     Outputs text data LENGTH bytes maximum.  If LENGTH is set to 0,
     `ebstopcode' outputs the whole text.  By default, the length is
     set to 2048.

`-n'
`--no-candidates'
     Suppress stop code candidates on output.

`-p PAGE:OFFSET'
`--text-position PAGE:OFFSET'
     Start outputting text data at this position.  PAGE must be a
     hexadecimal integer greater than 0, and OFFSET must be a
     hexadecimal integer between 0 and 0x7FF.  If the option is not
     specified, `ebstopcode' starts outputting at the beginning of text
     data.

`-v'
`--version'
     Output version number to standard out, then exit.

   `--code' (`-c') and `--length' (`-l') options override each other.



